# Governed UI Consumption (TIP-004)

Applies when composing `@afenda/ui` in **consumer** packages (`packages/appshell`, `apps/erp`).
For **authoring** primitives, use `.cursor/skills/govern-primitive/SKILL.md`.

## The rule

| Element | Styling |
|---------|---------|
| Plain HTML (`div`, `header`, `span`, `p`, `nav`) | Token utilities from `apps/erp/src/app/globals.css` |
| `@afenda/ui` primitives | **Governed props only** — `intent`, `emphasis`, `tone`, `size`, `variant`, `state` |
| shadcn-studio / registry blocks | Strip all `className` from governed imports before merge |

**Never** paste studio `className` strings onto `Button`, `DialogContent`, `SheetContent`, `DropdownMenu*`, `Sidebar*`, `Avatar`, `Badge`, `Tabs*`, `Combobox*`, etc. Runtime throws `TIP-004 className policy violation` in dev/tests.

## Correct patterns

```tsx
// ✅ shell chrome on plain wrapper
<div className="relative">
  <Button {...resolveStockButtonProps({ variant: "ghost", size: "icon-lg" })} />
  <span className="bg-destructive absolute size-2 rounded-full" aria-hidden />
</div>

// ✅ governed props — no className
<Badge emphasis="soft" tone="neutral">8 New</Badge>

// ❌ studio copy-paste
<SheetContent className="gap-0 sm:max-w-md [&>button]:top-2" />
```

## Imports

- Import primitives from `@afenda/ui`
- Import `resolveStockButtonProps` / governance helpers from `@afenda/ui/governance` **at call sites**
- **Do not** create local re-export barrels (`packages/appshell/src/governance/index.ts`)
- **Do not** add CSS modules for shell chrome when `globals.css` already sources the package

## shadcn-studio workflow

After installing or pasting a block:

1. Move block to `packages/appshell/src/shadcn-studio/blocks/` (not `packages/ui`)
2. Remove every `className` on `@afenda/ui` components
3. Keep semantic layout classes on plain HTML wrappers only
4. Run `pnpm --filter @afenda/appshell test:run`

## Verification

```bash
pnpm --filter @afenda/appshell test:run
pnpm --filter @afenda/ui check:governance   # when touching primitives
```

Static enforcement: `scripts/governance/governed-ui-consumption.mjs` (hook + appshell test).
